President Obama offers his condolences to Queen Sirikit, her family, and the people of Thailand on the passing of King Bhumibol Adulyadej. He describes the King as a close friend and valued partner of the United States, and recalls his grace, warmth, and compassion for the Thai people. The President acknowledges the King's tireless efforts to improve the standard of living for the Thai people and his innovative contributions to technology. President Obama expresses solidarity with the Thai people during this time of mourning.